    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-10-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-10-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.00/608.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to Russia</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Although the Chinese Chargé d’Affaires stated to me last night that the
                    revolution is purely local, confined to northern provinces, with all the south
                    tranquil. Neratoff regards affair in China as very serious, and says the reports
                    to him are that revolution is spreading. He appreciates the good will of the
                    United States, but as no foreign casualties are reported does not deem it
                    expedient to interfere. No Russian vessels have been sent to the scene of
                    disturbance, except one small gunboat.</p>
                <p>Otto Franke of Hamburg, Oriental expert, declares the outbreak derives from the
                    ancient hatred of one branch of the Mongolian race for another, rather than from
                    any genuine movement for reform or resistance to oppression.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Guild.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
